        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(outbound): bootstrap external channel plugins for cron announce delivery (#78754)",
        "body": "fix(cron): bootstrap external channel plugins for isolated session announce delivery\n\n## Summary\n\n- **Problem:** Cron jobs with `sessionTarget: \"isolated\"` + `delivery.mode: \"announce\"` + external channel (e.g., `openclaw-weixin`) fail with \"Unsupported channel\" because the cron delivery path cannot resolve npm-installed channel plugins.\n- **Fix:** When `resolveOutboundChannelPlugin` returns `undefined` but `allowBootstrap` is `true`, attempt plugin bootstrap via `loadOpenClawPlugins` to force fresh plugin discovery. Also add fallback in bootstrap runtime when cached registry lacks the channel.\n- **Out of scope:** No changes to bundled channel resolution or agentTurn delivery paths (which already work).\n\n## Linked context\n\nFixes #78754\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** Isolated session cron announce delivery fails for external channel plugins with \"Unsupported channel\" error.\n- **Real environment tested:** Windows 10, Node.js v22.22.3, OpenClaw latest main, local checkout with the patch applied.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n  ```bash\n  node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/infra/outbound/channel-resolution.test.ts src/infra/outbound/channel-bootstrap.runtime.test.ts\n  ```\n- **Evidence after fix:**\n  ```\n  [test] starting test/vitest/vitest.infra.config.ts\n\n   RUN  v4.1.8 D:/JavaUp/openclaw\n\n   Test Files  2 passed (2)\n        Tests  30 passed (30)\n     Start at  21:03:57\n     Duration  4.17s (transform 1.17s, setup 611ms, import 2.05s, tests 1.17s)\n\n  [test] passed 1 Vitest shard in 11.23s\n  ```\n- **Observed result after fix:** 30 tests pass including 4 new regression tests covering external channel bootstrap and loadOpenClawPlugins fallback.\n- **What was not tested:** Live cron job with real external channel plugin. Tests use mocked plugin registry and bootstrap functions.\n\n## Regression Test Plan\n\n- Coverage level: Unit test\n- Target test file: `src/infra/outbound/channel-resolution.test.ts`, `src/infra/outbound/channel-bootstrap.runtime.test.ts`\n- Scenario locked in: External channel plugin bootstrap on first use\n- Why this is the smallest reliable guardrail: Tests verify the bootstrap trigger and fallback logic without requiring a live external channel.\n\n## Root Cause\n\n- Root cause: Cron delivery channel resolution only looks up bundled channels, not npm-installed external plugins\n- Missing detection / guardrail: No bootstrap trigger when channel plugin is not found in cached registry\n",
